const hardWaterNarrative = {
  headline: 'Hard Water in Chino Hills — What It Does to Your Appliances',
  paragraphs: [
    "This is the conversation we have on almost every service call in Chino Hills. Hard water — water with high concentrations of dissolved calcium and magnesium — is the single biggest factor driving appliance wear in this city. Most homeowners have no idea it's happening until something stops working.",
  ],
  subSections: [
    {
      title: 'Dishwashers',
      paragraphs: [
        "Hard water deposits accumulate in the spray arm ports, filter assembly, and door gasket on a predictable timeline. In a coastal city with softer water, you can go 12–18 months between filter cleanings. In Chino Hills, the filter should be cleaned every 3 months. The spray arm ports should be cleared every 6 months. If your glasses have a white film or etch marks, that's calcium. If your dishwasher is leaving dishes dirty, clean the filter before assuming anything is broken — nine times out of ten in this area, that's the issue.",
        "The Bosch E24 drain error is endemic here. It means the dishwasher can't drain — and the first diagnosis in every Chino Hills home is the filter, not the pump. A pump replacement costs $250–$350. A filter cleaning costs $89. We find the cheaper fix first.",
      ],
    },
    {
      title: 'Ice Makers',
      paragraphs: [
        "Scale buildup inside the ice maker mold is a slow process that most people never notice — until the ice cubes start tasting off, come out cloudy, or production drops dramatically. We descale ice makers as part of every ice maker repair call in San Bernardino County. If you have a refrigerator with a built-in ice maker and you've never had it serviced, and you've lived in Chino Hills for more than three years, it's worth a look.",
      ],
    },
    {
      title: 'Washing Machines',
      paragraphs: [
        "Hard water leaves mineral deposits in the drum, door gasket, and detergent dispenser of front-loading washers. Over time, this contributes to the mold and odor problems that Samsung and LG front-loaders are known for in hard water areas. Monthly drum cleaning with a washing machine cleaner is not optional in Chino Hills — it's maintenance. We also see detergent dispenser blockages and door gasket hardening accelerated by scale accumulation.",
      ],
    },
    {
      title: 'Refrigerator Water Filters',
      paragraphs: [
        "Manufacturer recommendation is every 6 months. In Chino Hills hard water, every 4 months is more appropriate. A saturated filter doesn't just reduce water quality — it restricts flow to the ice maker and can contribute to ice maker failures. We replace filters on almost every refrigerator call here and recommend customers put a recurring reminder in their phone.",
      ],
    },
    {
      title: 'Maintenance Schedule for Chino Hills Homes',
      paragraphs: [
        "<strong>Dishwasher filter:</strong> Every 3 months — run hot water + white vinegar cycle monthly.<br><strong>Refrigerator water filter:</strong> Every 4 months (not 6).<br><strong>Ice maker descale:</strong> Every 12–18 months, or when cubes turn cloudy.<br><strong>Washing machine drum clean:</strong> Monthly with cleaner tablet.<br><strong>Condenser coils (canyon/hillside homes):</strong> Every 6–9 months.<br><strong>Outdoor refrigerator coils:</strong> Every 4–6 months.",
      ],
    },
  ],
};

const housingStockNarrative = {
  headline: "What's in Chino Hills Homes — Appliance Profile by Neighborhood",
  paragraphs: [
    "Chino Hills is primarily a 2000–2015 build city, which puts most of the housing stock in the appliance failure window. Appliances installed when the homes were built are now 10–20 years old. Appliances upgraded in the 2010s are 8–12 years old. Both generations are showing up on our schedule regularly.",
  ],
  subSections: [
    {
      title: 'Butterfield Ranch & Eucalyptus Hills — Upper Tier',
      paragraphs: [
        "These are the larger homes — 3,000–5,000 square feet on hillside lots with views. The kitchens tend to have Sub-Zero or Thermador refrigerators, Wolf ranges, and KitchenAid or Bosch dishwashers. Wine coolers and beverage centers are common. Outdoor kitchens with refrigerators and ice makers are standard in the newer builds. We treat these calls the same as our Beverly Hills and Bel Air work — OEM parts, careful handling, no aftermarket substitutes. Sub-Zero condenser cleaning in canyon-adjacent homes here should be every 6 months.",
