    {
      title: 'Rolling Ridge & Payne Ranch — Mid-Tier Planned Communities',
      paragraphs: [
        "Solid planned community housing — 2,000–3,500 sq ft, built primarily 2000–2012. Samsung, LG, and Whirlpool dominate. These are the homes where we see the most hard water-related dishwasher and ice maker calls. The LG linear inverter compressor failures from the 2012–2018 generation show up regularly here. We keep Samsung French-door OEM parts and LG start relay assemblies stocked specifically for this part of the Inland Empire.",
      ],
    },
    {
      title: 'Los Serranos — Older Stock',
      paragraphs: [
        "Los Serranos is the oldest part of Chino Hills — original housing stock from the 1950s and '60s, still largely intact. Appliances here are a mix of older Whirlpool and GE that have been in service for 20+ years and mid-range replacements from the 2000s and '10s. We often get calls here to assess whether it's worth repairing a 15-year-old fridge or washer. Our honest answer: if the compressor or motor is sound, older appliances without control boards often outlast the replacement.",
      ],
    },
    {
      title: 'Carbon Canyon & Hillside Roads — Canyon Homes',
      paragraphs: [
        "Carbon Canyon Road properties and the elevated streets off Chino Hills Parkway see the most particulate exposure from Santa Ana wind events. Condenser coils on every appliance clog faster here. Outdoor kitchens are particularly vulnerable — a beverage center sitting on a patio exposed to canyon winds needs coil cleaning every 4–5 months. We also see more vent-related dryer issues here, as homes often have longer external vent runs to manage hillside architecture.",
      ],
    },
  ],
};

